<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Respect and a$$holery are the karma of eq, they both come back at your three times what you put into it from others.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Interesting pair of quotes. Let's try looking at it in another light: So what if Clan X lost it and starting ranting and showed no respect or courtesy to us... the fact that we had taken a camp they had called but not actually moved into and left standing for an hour gives them some righteous priority to flame us without fear of the loss of respect they'll get in our eyes for their indecency? Could that, perhaps, have contributed to the degineration of events? A lack of courtesy in /ooc?<br>
<br>
I'm glad Rixma is finally off flaming Xedd and LOM as a whole, because they never were at fault. The leadership certainly was involved throughout the entire process - I am part of it. I'll respect a camp that's occupied, but it is a waste of resources to call a camp and then sit around at zone in for an hour. Next time you want the east wing and call it, be sure to actually enter it.<br>
<br>
Am I being a little hard on Clan X? Yes. Flaming someone is not the way to earn their respect. Crying about a camp you left untended for over an hour is also not a way to earn their respect. I'd rather respect Clan X than be disgusted with their attitude and lack of courtesy. I don't appreciate being called &quot;loot whore, all you care about loot&quot; by people who want me to move so they can have the loot that, as of yet, they have not worked for - just dawdled at zone in. The hypocrisy and small mindedness of this approach irritates me. I'm not a mean guy, I think my record pretty much clearly states that. But coming to the RTA and flaming me after flaming me in game and in tells for taking a camp you never occupied strikes me as ludicrous, and I'd like to keep the record set straight.<br>
<br>
