<br>
Clan X in claiming the East Wing (and at best making a token effort to support the claim) is asking LOM to be considerate and leave the camp alone until the rest of the Clan X force arrives to start working the camp completely.  The LOM group moves past these waiting folks, and are perceived as 'greedy' and 'inconsiderate' for not respecting the Clan X claim.<br>
<br>
There is another side to this humanity:<br>
<br>
LOM sees a group arrive early to claim a camp they are not capable (or not intending) to do on their own.  Clan X says the people that remained COULD HAVE done east wing alone.  The fact remains that they DID NOT, and were waiting for greater forces.  This 'prime' camp is going un-used, or minimally, extremely under used, for an extended time.  This is perceived as 'greedy' and thus 'inconsiderate' by the LOM group.<br>
<br>
Neither group acted without fault. So what we are being asked to weigh is &quot;Who is more wrong?&quot;  Yes, that is certainly humanity at work.<br>
